# TypeScript Package Rules

## Directory Structure

Every package in `packages/` MUST follow this exact layout:

```
packages/<name>/
  src/
    index.ts              <- barrel file, re-exports all public API
    lib/
      types.ts            <- interfaces and type aliases
      <feature>.ts        <- implementation
  package.json            <- must have scope tag, @pipefx/source export condition
  tsconfig.json           <- references tsconfig.lib.json + tsconfig.spec.json
  tsconfig.lib.json       <- build config
  tsconfig.spec.json      <- test config
  vite.config.ts          <- vitest runner
```

## Import Rules

- ALWAYS use `.js` extensions in relative imports: `import { foo } from './lib/bar.js'`
- NEVER use extensionless imports: `import { foo } from './lib/bar'` -- this will fail at runtime with ESM.
- Import workspace packages by name: `import { ConnectorRegistry } from '@pipefx/connectors'`
- NEVER use relative paths to reach into other packages (e.g., `../../packages/connectors/src/...`).
- Use `import type { ... }` for type-only imports to avoid runtime overhead.

## Exports

- The `src/index.ts` barrel file is the ONLY public API surface. Everything else is internal.
- Re-export types with `export type { ... }` in the barrel.
- Re-export implementations with `export { ... }` in the barrel.

## Dependencies

- External deps go in the package's own `package.json`, not the root.
- Workspace deps use `"workspace:*"` protocol: `"@pipefx/connectors": "workspace:*"`.
- Every package must include `"tslib": "^2.3.0"` in dependencies (required by `importHelpers`).
- Root `package.json` should only contain devDependencies (build tools, Nx, TypeScript, etc.).

## Nx Tags and Module Boundaries

- Every package MUST have a `scope:<name>` tag in its `package.json` under `nx.tags`.
- Dependency rules are in `eslint.config.mjs`. When creating a new package, add a corresponding `depConstraints` entry.
- Dependencies flow downward only. Circular dependencies are forbidden.

## Verification

After any change to a package, run:
```
pnpm nx run-many -t build lint typecheck -p @pipefx/<name>
```
